Photo, Rescue From Flames: Paramedics give oxygen to Jeanie Buford after she 
was rescued from the fourth floor of a burning six-story office building at 
1250 Wilshire Blvd. At right, a firefighter climbs down the ladder on which 
Buford was led to safety. The fire, which broke out at 11:39 a.m. Wednesday, 
was contained within 40 minutes and there were no injuries, Fire Department 
spokeswoman Denise Alvarado said. The cause is under investigation. Buford said 
she was among several residents of the dilapidated 60-year-old building, though 
fire officials said they were aware of only four who escaped the property. 
Building and fire officials said they would be investigating its use, and that 
the owner, Chase Pulec Joint Venture, could face charges for allowing 
residential occupants in a commercial building. KEN LUBAS / Los Angeles Times 
</P>
