<P>
SOUTHERN SECTION SOFTBALL ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
LA HABRA STOPS FOOTHILL IN 12 INNINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Cathy Turner doubled in a run in the 12th inning to give La Habra High School a 
3-2 victory over Foothill in a Southern Section 4-A Division wild-card softball 
playoff game Wednesday at La Habra. 
</P>
<P>
Turner's double drove in freshman Danielle Ortega, who led off the inning with 
a single. 
</P>
<P>
Ortega also drove in the tying run with a two-out single in the bottom of the 
seventh, and pitched a complete game, striking out six and allowing six hits 
and no walks. 
</P>
<P>
La Habra (15-11) took a 1-0 lead in the sixth before Foothill (17-12) scored 
twice in the seventh. 
</P>
<P>
In a 1-A wild-card game: 
</P>
<P>
Calvary Chapel 9, Connelly 1 -- Georgie Bogert pitched a six-hitter, struck out 
nine and walked none to lead Calvary Chapel (8-5-1) over Connelly (4-6) at 
Davis Park in Costa Mesa. Venise Garcia had two hits, scored twice and had four 
RBIs. 
</P>
