<HEADLINE>
<P>
SPORTS ET CETERA: UCSD WOMEN LOSE TENNIS FINAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The defending champion UC San Diego women's tennis team lost to Gustavus 
Adolphus, 5-4, Wednesday in the championship match of the NCAA Division III 
championships at Trenton, N.J. 
</P>
<P>
The match was played indoors because of rain, UCSD's first indoor match this 
season. 
</P>
<P>
The deciding match was No. 3 doubles, where Molly McCormick and Heidi Rostberg 
defeated UCSD's Amanda Lynch and Kristen Diels, 4-6, 6-4, 7-6, (7-2). 
</P>
<P>
UCSD (16-5), which was ranked No. 1 in Division III and seeded No. 1 in the 
tournament, swept the first three singles. At No. 1, Christine Behrens defeated 
Amy McCrea, 6-3, 4-6, 6-4. Robyn Inada defeated Mary Sutherland of Gustavus 
Adolphus, 6-4, 5-7, 6-1, at No. 2, and UCSD's Susan Carney defeated Nikki 
LaVoi, 7-5, 6-2, at No. 3. 
</P>
<P>
During the regular season, UCSD defeated Gustavus Adolphus, 8-1. 
</P>
<P>
Individual singles and doubles competition begins today. Behrens is seeded 
second in singles and, she and Carney are seeded second in doubles behind 
McCrea and Sutherland. 
</P>
</TEXT>
