<HEADLINE>
<P>
WESTSIDE DIGEST: BRENTWOOD; 
</P>
<P>
DWP FACILITY OPEN HOUSE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
City Councilman Marvin Braude will join Los Angeles Department of Water and 
Power officials at the opening of a new electrical facility at Sunset Boulevard 
and Church Lane in Brentwood from 10 a.m. to noon Saturday. The public is 
invited. 
</P>
<P>
The open house will include tours of the facility, as well as informational 
exhibits, entertainment and refreshments, a DWP spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
The facility, which began operating last September, was built to relieve demand 
on nearby distributing stations and improve the reliability of electrical 
service in the area, project manager Ralph Jones said. It serves an area 
bounded by Mulholland Drive on the north, Wilshire and San Vicente boulevards 
on the south, Westwood Boulevard on the east and Bundy Drive on the west, he 
said. 
</P>
