<HEADLINE>
<P>
11TH ANNUAL ART WALK IN VENICE PLANNED TO RAISE FUNDS FOR CLINIC 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Visitors to the 11th annual Art Walk on Sunday will be able to look inside the 
studios of the artists of Venice and feed on the creations of some of the 
city's culinary artists. 
</P>
<P>
The Art Walk is the major fund-raiser for the Venice Family Clinic. 
</P>
<P>
Last year, the event drew 5,000 people. 
</P>
<P>
A $45 ticket entitles the buyer to walk through the studios of more than 50 
artists, including Charles Arnoldi, Martha Alf, Laddie John Dill, Fritz 
Scholder, Ruth Weisberg and Susan Hauptman. The artists' media range from oil 
painting to neon sculpture. There are also 24 special exhibits, including 
"Artists in the Backroom," a display of art by budding artists who work in 
galleries. 
</P>
<P>
More than 300 works of art will be offered for sale at a silent auction at 
Westminister Elementary School, 1010 W. Washington Blvd., where tickets can be 
purchased Sunday. To buy tickets in advance, call (213) 392-8630. The school is 
the starting place for the walk. 
</P>
<P>
A separate component of the Art Walk on Saturday and Sunday will be guided 
docent tours, for a contribution of $90, of selected studios and the 
neighborhood. 
</P>
<P>
At the annual Art Walk dinner Saturday night at Santa Monica Airport, 
pediatrician Walter M. Tasem and restaurateurs Rebecca and Bruce Marder, owners 
of Rebecca's and the West Beach Cafe, will be honored. 
</P>
<P>
All proceeds from the Venice Art Walk go to the Venice Family Clinic, which 
provides medical care for the uninsured, working poor and homeless. About 
10,000 patients are served at the clinic each year. The Art Walk provides about 
one-quarter of the clinic's funding. 
</P>
<P>
For more information, call (213) 392-WALK. 
</P>
