<HEADLINE>
<P>
TAIWAN OFFERS TALKS WITH CHINA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
TAIPEI, Taiwan 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The government of Taiwan would welcome talks with China, the presidential 
spokesman said Wednesday, which could pave the way for closer ties with 
Beijing. 
</P>
<P>
President Lee Teng-hui, in a meeting Tuesday with lawmakers who had just 
returned from China, said he favors government-to-government dialogue between 
Taiwan and China. 
</P>
<P>
Lee ruled out talks between the Chinese Communist Party and Taiwan's ruling 
Nationalist Party. 
</P>
<P>
He also said talks could not be held until Beijing rules out the use of force 
against Taiwan and stops trying to isolate it diplomatically. 
</P>
<P>
There was no immediate comment from China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
