<HEADLINE>
<P>
2 JUDGES APPOINTED TO L.A. SUPERIOR COURT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Gov. George Deukmejian has announced two appointments to the Los Angeles County 
Superior Court. Municipal Judge Patti S. Kitching, 48, of Palos Verdes Estates, 
will replace Judge Robert B. Lopez, who retired. 
</P>
<P>
Municipal Judge Judith L. Champagne, 45, of Santa Monica, will replace Judge 
Vernon G. Foster, who also retired. 
</P>
<P>
Kitching has degrees from UCLA and Loyola, and has been a deputy attorney 
general in Los Angeles as well as senior counsel for the Bank of America. 
Champagne also has degrees from UCLA and Loyola. She practiced law in the 
Hawthorne-area for two years and was deputy district attorney for 10 years. 
</P>
<P>
Deukmejian also named William R. Weisman, 42, of Long Beach, to the Municipal 
Court bench in Los Angeles, replacing Judge Sandy Kriegler, who was elevated to 
the Superior Court. Weisman has degrees from Cal State Northridge and Loyola. 
He has been a deputy attorney general since 1973. 
</P>
</TEXT>
