<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: CHULA VISTA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 51-year-old man was arrested Wednesday on suspicion of shooting his 
38-year-old wife in the face, police said. 
</P>
<P>
Police, responding to a report of shots being fired, arrived about 12:40 a.m. 
at a residence in the 700 block of F Street, and saw Lee Thomas carrying his 
bleeding wife from the apartment. She suffered a gunshot wound to the face and 
is in fair condition at UC San Diego Medical Center, a hospital spokeswoman 
said. 
</P>
<P>
Thomas was being held at County Jail on suspicion of assault with a deadly 
weapon. 
</P>
</TEXT>
