<BYLINE>
<P>
By ROB FERNAS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Top-seeded Mira Costa High will travel to meet Newport Harbor at 7:30 tonight 
in the quarterfinals of the Southern Section 4-A boys' volleyball playoffs. 
</P>
<P>
The match was moved up a day because Newport Harbor's prom is Friday night. 
</P>
<P>
"I wouldn't want them laboring under that problem," said Mira Costa Coach Mike 
Cook, who had to agree to the change. "If my kids had the prom that night, I 
would hope my opponent would allow us to have the game early. Maybe someone 
will do me a favor someday." 
</P>
<P>
Newport Harbor (11-5), which won the 4-A title in 1987, is led by setter Alex 
Opoulos, freshman outside hitter Mark McAnlis and 6-foot-3 middle blocker Ian 
Juberg. The Sailors defeated Leuzinger in the first round Friday, 12-15, 15-4, 
15-6, 15-4. 
</P>
<P>
Mira Costa (19-0) advanced with a 15-4, 15-5, 15-6 victory over Dos Pueblos of 
Goleta. The Mustangs have four players who have signed with major colleges: 
outside hitter David Swatik (UCLA), middle blockers Pat Ivie and Mike 
Ashenfelter (USC) and setter Canyon Ceman (Stanford). ROB FERNAS 
