</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Southern Pacific May Leave San Francisco: Southern Pacific Transportation Co. 
may sell its downtown headquarters and transfer some or all of its 1,800 
workers out of San Francisco, spokesman Jim Loveland said. 
</P>
<P>
The sale could help relieve the company's burden of about $500 million in 
acquisition debt. But Loveland said offers for the building triggered the 
company's review of a possible sale. "We're going to analyze the process by 
which we might sell the building and move to less expensive headquarters -- 
possibly in the Bay Area or possibly outside," Loveland said. 
</P>
