<P>
Majority of Companies Test for Drug Abuse: More than half of the corporations 
in a recent survey said they test job applicants or employees for substance 
abuse or are about to begin testing, the Conference Board reported. 
</P>
<P>
Almost two-thirds said they believed that they now have a safer work 
environment, the survey said. The research groups survey showed 55% of the 
companies questioned said they test, or are about to begin testing, job 
applicants or employees. The Conference Board surveyed 681 corporate human 
resources executives in a range of industries. 
</P>
