<HEADLINE>
<P>
SCHOOL NEWS: DAMIEN HIGH SCHOOL OPEN HOUSE PLANNED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The dedication ceremony and open house for a 13,000-square-foot addition to the 
Damien High School campus will be held at 3 p.m. Saturday at the campus, 1124 
Bonita Ave., La Verne. 
</P>
<P>
The two-story combination classroom-office building features science and 
computer labs, classrooms, office space, and a chapel and conference room. 
</P>
<P>
The facility was built with $1.2 million in pledges and gifts from parents and 
alumni and a loan from the Archdiocese of Los Angeles. 
</P>
<P>
The goal of the school's Tradition Continues Campaign is to raise $2.3 million 
for added library space, faculty endowments, a swimming pool, tennis courts and 
physical improvements to the campus. 
</P>
</TEXT>
