<HEADLINE>
<P>
NAMES IN THE NEWS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UCLA softball pitcher Lisa Longaker and her coach, Sharron Backus, were named 
player and coach of the year in the Pacific-10 Conference. It is the third time 
Longaker has won the honor. 
</P>
<P>
UCLA selections on the all-conference first team in addition to Longaker, a 
senior, were junior infielder Kerry Dienelt, freshman infielder Kristy Howard, 
junior outfielder Shanna Flynn, sophomore outfielder Yvonne Gutierrez and 
freshman utility player Lisa Fernandez. 
</P>
<P>
Bruins on the second team were sophomore catcher Kelly Inouye, junior infielder 
Missy Phillips and senior outfielder Michelle Montgomery. 
</P>
<P>
UCLA volleyball player Trevor Schirman has been named to the 1990 All-Western 
Intercollegiate Volleyball Assn. team selected by conference coaches and 
players. Schirman is a senior middle blocker from Waimanolo, Hawaii. 
</P>
<P>
Second-team selections included junior outside hitter Sto Saipaia of Loyola 
Marymount, freshman middle blocker Tom Sorenson of Pepperdine and senior setter 
Parker Blackman of Stanford, who lives in Santa Monica. Chris Young of Loyola 
received honorable mention. 
</P>
<P>
Nine baseball players have signed letters of intent with Pepperdine. They 
include pitcher Pat Ahearne of Los Angeles Harbor College, pitcher Jerry 
Aschoff of Rancho Santiago College, catcher Keven Dell'Amico of Loyola High 
School, pitcher Mauricio Estivil of Culver City High School and pitcher Curt 
Gossett of Glendora High School. 
</P>
<P>
Others are pitcher Sky Lasowitz of Los Angeles Harbor College, infielder Damon 
Lembi of Burlingame High School, infielder-outfielder Lance Marks of Dana Hills 
High School and outfielder George Paz of Claremont High School. 
</P>
<P>
Jay Pittman and David Belfer won the A flight in the Penmar Men's Golf Club's 
pairs match-play championships. B-flight winners were Herb Cohn and Bob 
Gotthoffer. 
</P>
</TEXT>
