<HEADLINE>
<P>
NO WINNER -- LOTTO AT $17 MILLION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The $10.4-million jackpot in the California Lottery Lotto 6/49 game went 
unclaimed Wednesday night and will roll over to an estimated $17 million for 
Saturday night's drawing, Lotto officials said. 
</P>
<P>
The winning numbers chosen in the 6/49 game were 48, 35, 41, 8, 18, 9, and the 
bonus number, 13. 
</P>
<P>
There were six tickets with five of six winning numbers and the bonus number. 
They are worth $254,065 each and split a $1.5-million prize pool. 
</P>
<P>
There were 263 tickets with five of six numbers, and they win $2,986 each. The 
tickets divided a prize pool of $785,000. 
</P>
</TEXT>
