<P>
TRADE MISSION TO EASTERN BLOC 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
WASHINGTON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Commerce Secretary Robert A. Mosbacher said today that the United States plans 
to send a telecommunications mission to Czechoslovakia and Hungary in June. 
</P>
<P>
In testimony before a House telecommunications subcommittee, he said the trip 
will allow officials from U.S. telecommunications equipment and services 
companies to meet with trade and telecommunications experts in Eastern European 
countries. 
</P>
<P>
A similar trip was undertaken to Warsaw in February, Mosbacher said. 
</P>
