<HEADLINE>
<P>
SHORT TAKES; 
</P>
<P>
SATCHMO TRIBUTE TO OPEN FESTIVAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEWPORT, R.I. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 90th birthday tribute to late jazz trumpet master Louis Armstrong will open 
this year's Newport Jazz Festival, producers said today. 
</P>
<P>
The Aug. 17-19 event, formally known as the JVC Jazz Festival-Newport, will 
mark the festival's 10th year back in Newport. 
</P>
<P>
The original Newport Jazz Festival was held from 1954 to 1971, when a riot by 
gate-crashing rowdies moved the event to New York. 
</P>
<P>
Trumpeter Wynton Marsalis will produce the jazz festival's Aug. 17 Armstrong 
tribute, featuring Marsalis and New Orleans musicians, along with trumpeters 
Doc Cheatham, Ruby Braff and Jon Faddis and singer Carrie Smith. Actor Ossie 
Davis will act as host for the evening. 
</P>
<P>
Saturday's lineup features Miles Davis, Gerry Mulligan, B. B. King, Elvin Jones 
and Latin jazz artists Celia Cruz and Tito Puente. Sunday's finale will feature 
George Benson, McCoy Tyner, Harry Connick Jr., the Count Basie Orchestra, the 
Phil Woods Quartet and fusion keyboard innovator Joe Zawinul. 
</P>
</TEXT>
