NAMES IN THE NEWS; 
</P>
<P>
DRUG CZAR SNIPES AT 'SIMPSONS' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
PITTSBURGH 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
g czar William J. Bennett, who is on a crusade against crack dealers, took a 
swipe at a celluloid bad boy -- Bart Simpson. 
</P>
<P>
During a tour Wednesday of the Foundation for Abraxas drug-treatment center, 
Bennett spied a poster of the cartoon miscreant and told recovering addicts 
that they shouldn't follow Bart's lead as an underachiever. 
</P>
<P>
"You guys aren't watching 'The Simpsons,' are you? That's not going to help you 
any," said Bennett, director of the national drug policy office. 
</P>
<P>
Bart is the spike-haired son on "The Simpsons," the Fox network's highly rated 
cartoon sitcom featuring the adventures of a bug-eyed family of five. 
</P>
<P>
"We have great respect for Mr. Bennett's task and responsibility," said Brad 
Turell, a spokesman for the show. "But I am not aware of any one TV program 
that will help teen-agers kick the drug habit." 
</P>
</TEXT>
