<P>
SUPER FAN TRIUMPHS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
LOUISVILLE, Ky. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Super Fan caught the leaders coming out of the backstretch, then ran through 
heavy rain over the soft turf course to win the $35,200 Regret Prep by 1 1/2 
lengths Wednesday at Churchill Downs. Super Fan, under Keith Allen, covered the 
mile in 1:40 4-5 and paid $3.20, $2.20 and $2.10. The 3-year-old filly, owned 
by Warner L. Jones Jr., earned $24,310, increasing her winnings to $126,163 for 
her sixth win in 13 starts. 
</P>
